"07_largeinteger.mst — LargeInteger (sprint_s06_detail.md #07). Representation
 (pinned): the object's OWN IndexableBytes body IS the magnitude — base-256
 digits, little-endian, index 1 = least significant (byteAt:/byteAt:put:/
 size bind directly to the raw bytes primitives). Sign = the concrete class.
 fromSmallInteger: never takes an absolute value (Pitfall P3: SmallInteger
 minVal's negation overflows) — it peels two's-complement digits directly."

"I am the abstract arbitrary-precision integer. My indexable bytes ARE
 my magnitude — base-256 digits, least significant first — and my sign
 is my concrete class: LargePositiveInteger or LargeNegativeInteger. I
 exist so SmallInteger arithmetic can overflow safely; results are
 normalized back to SmallInteger whenever they fit, so you rarely meet
 me directly. I support +, -, *, comparison, divMod:, negated, asDouble
 and decimal printing. Full large // and \\ division is not
 implemented — only divMod:."

Integer subclass: LargeInteger [
    isInteger [
        ^true
    ]
    byteAt: i [
        <primitive: 40>
    ]
    byteAt: i put: v [
        <primitive: 41>
    ]
    size [
        <primitive: 28>
    ]
    asLargeInteger [
        ^self
    ]
    classSign [
        ^self class == LargePositiveInteger ifTrue: [ 1 ] ifFalse: [ -1 ]
    ]

    LargeInteger class >> copyDigitsFrom: aLarge [
        | r n |
        n := aLarge size.
        r := self basicNew: n.
        1 to: n do: [:i | r byteAt: i put: (aLarge byteAt: i) ].
        ^r
    ]

    "n >= 0: peel magnitude digits directly. n < 0: peel via floored //,\\
     (never overflows, even at minVal) collecting the low bytes of the
     two's-complement of |n|, then invert+add-1 to recover the magnitude."
    LargeInteger class >> fromSmallInteger: n [
        | count v result i more q d carry j inv s |
        n >= 0
            ifTrue: [
                count := 0. v := n.
                [ v = 0 ] whileFalse: [ count := count + 1. v := v // 256 ].
                count = 0 ifTrue: [ count := 1 ].
                result := LargePositiveInteger basicNew: count.
                v := n. i := 1.
                [ v = 0 ] whileFalse: [
                    result byteAt: i put: (v \\ 256).
                    v := v // 256.
                    i := i + 1 ].
                ^result ]
            ifFalse: [
                count := 0. v := n. more := true.
                [ more ] whileTrue: [
                    v := v // 256.
                    count := count + 1.
                    v = -1 ifTrue: [ more := false ] ].
                result := LargePositiveInteger basicNew: count.
                v := n. i := 1. more := true.
                [ more ] whileTrue: [
                    q := v // 256.
                    d := v - (q * 256).
                    result byteAt: i put: d.
                    v := q.
                    i := i + 1.
                    v = -1 ifTrue: [ more := false ] ].
                carry := 1. j := 1.
                [ j <= count ] whileTrue: [
                    inv := 255 - (result byteAt: j).
                    s := inv + carry.
                    result byteAt: j put: (s \\ 256).
                    carry := s // 256.
                    j := j + 1 ].
                "No normalize: fromSmallInteger: must always answer a real
                 LargeInteger (arithmetic fallbacks rely on its classSign/
                 size/byteAt: protocol), matching the positive branch."
                ^LargeNegativeInteger copyDigitsFrom: result ]
    ]

    "Trim a padded/over-allocated magnitude down to n significant bytes,
     preserving concrete class (sign). addMagnitude:/* always over-allocate
     by a carry byte, so results need re-canonicalizing before any
     size-sensitive comparison (compareMagnitude:) can trust them."
    trimmedTo: n [
        | r i |
        n = self size ifTrue: [ ^self ].
        r := self class basicNew: n.
        i := 1.
        [ i <= n ] whileTrue: [ r byteAt: i put: (self byteAt: i). i := i + 1 ].
        ^r
    ]

    "Fold high-to-low with a pre-shift bound check so the fold itself
     never overflows a smi; track the highest nonzero byte along the way
     so a too-big-for-smi result can still be trimmed to its canonical
     (no leading zero byte) size. Answer the demoted SmallInteger if it fits."
    normalize [
        | v i sz |
        v := 0.
        i := self size.
        sz := 0.
        [ i >= 1 ] whileTrue: [
            (sz = 0 and: [ (self byteAt: i) ~= 0 ]) ifTrue: [ sz := i ].
            v > (SmallInteger maxVal bitShift: -8) ifTrue: [ ^self trimmedTo: sz ].
            v := (v bitShift: 8) + (self byteAt: i).
            i := i - 1 ].
        self classSign = 1
            ifTrue: [ ^v <= SmallInteger maxVal ifTrue: [ v ] ifFalse: [ self trimmedTo: sz ] ]
            ifFalse: [ ^(0 - v) >= SmallInteger minVal ifTrue: [ 0 - v ] ifFalse: [ self trimmedTo: sz ] ]
    ]

    addMagnitude: b [
        | m n r i da db s c |
        m := self size. n := b size.
        r := LargePositiveInteger basicNew: (m max: n) + 1.
        c := 0. i := 1.
        [ i <= r size ] whileTrue: [
            da := i <= m ifTrue: [ self byteAt: i ] ifFalse: [ 0 ].
            db := i <= n ifTrue: [ b byteAt: i ] ifFalse: [ 0 ].
            s := da + db + c.
            r byteAt: i put: (s \\ 256).
            c := s // 256.
            i := i + 1 ].
        ^r
    ]

    "self magnitude - b magnitude; requires |self| >= |b|."
    subMagnitude: b [
        | m n r i da db s borrow |
        m := self size. n := b size.
        r := LargePositiveInteger basicNew: m.
        borrow := 0. i := 1.
        [ i <= m ] whileTrue: [
            da := self byteAt: i.
            db := i <= n ifTrue: [ b byteAt: i ] ifFalse: [ 0 ].
            s := da - db - borrow.
            s < 0 ifTrue: [ s := s + 256. borrow := 1 ] ifFalse: [ borrow := 0 ].
            r byteAt: i put: s.
            i := i + 1 ].
        ^r
    ]

    compareMagnitude: b [
        | m n i |
        m := self size. n := b size.
        m > n ifTrue: [ ^1 ].
        m < n ifTrue: [ ^-1 ].
        i := m.
        [ i >= 1 ] whileTrue: [
            (self byteAt: i) > (b byteAt: i) ifTrue: [ ^1 ].
            (self byteAt: i) < (b byteAt: i) ifTrue: [ ^-1 ].
            i := i - 1 ].
        ^0
    ]

    "self must be a magnitude-only (LargePositiveInteger-class) scratch
     value; wraps it in the requested sign's class and normalizes."
    withSign: s [
        s = 1 ifTrue: [ ^self normalize ].
        ^(LargeNegativeInteger copyDigitsFrom: self) normalize
    ]

    + other [
        | b |
        other isDouble ifTrue: [ ^self asDouble + other ].
        b := other asLargeInteger.
        self classSign = b classSign
            ifTrue: [ ^(self addMagnitude: b) withSign: self classSign ]
            ifFalse: [
                (self compareMagnitude: b) >= 0
                    ifTrue: [ ^(self subMagnitude: b) withSign: self classSign ]
                    ifFalse: [ ^(b subMagnitude: self) withSign: b classSign ] ]
    ]
    - other [
        other isDouble ifTrue: [ ^self asDouble - other ].
        ^self + other asLargeInteger negated
    ]
    * other [
        | b m n r i j t c |
        other isDouble ifTrue: [ ^self asDouble * other ].
        b := other asLargeInteger.
        m := self size. n := b size.
        r := LargePositiveInteger basicNew: m + n.
        i := 1.
        [ i <= m ] whileTrue: [
            c := 0. j := 1.
            [ j <= n ] whileTrue: [
                t := (r byteAt: i + j - 1) + ((self byteAt: i) * (b byteAt: j)) + c.
                r byteAt: (i + j - 1) put: (t \\ 256).
                c := t // 256.
                j := j + 1 ].
            [ c > 0 ] whileTrue: [
                t := (r byteAt: i + j - 1) + c.
                r byteAt: (i + j - 1) put: (t \\ 256).
                c := t // 256.
                j := j + 1 ].
            i := i + 1 ].
        ^r withSign: self classSign * b classSign
    ]
    negated [
        self classSign = 1
            ifTrue: [ ^(LargeNegativeInteger copyDigitsFrom: self) normalize ]
            ifFalse: [ ^(LargePositiveInteger copyDigitsFrom: self) normalize ]
    ]
    < other [
        | b |
        other isDouble ifTrue: [ ^self asDouble < other ].
        b := other asLargeInteger.
        self classSign ~= b classSign ifTrue: [ ^self classSign < b classSign ].
        self classSign = 1
            ifTrue: [ ^(self compareMagnitude: b) < 0 ]
            ifFalse: [ ^(self compareMagnitude: b) > 0 ]
    ]
    = other [
        other isDouble ifTrue: [ ^self asDouble = other ].
        (other isKindOf: LargeInteger) ifFalse: [
            other isInteger ifTrue: [ ^self = other asLargeInteger ].
            ^false ].
        ^(self classSign = other classSign) and: [ (self compareMagnitude: other) = 0 ]
    ]
    hash [
        <primitive: 44>
    ]
    asDouble [
        | v i |
        v := 0.0.
        i := self size.
        [ i >= 1 ] whileTrue: [
            v := (v * 256.0) + (self byteAt: i) asDouble.
            i := i - 1 ].
        ^self classSign = 1 ifTrue: [ v ] ifFalse: [ v negated ]
    ]

    "Magnitude-only divmod by a smi divisor 1 < d <= 255 — printOn:'s only
     consumer (repeated /10); self must already be non-negative."
    divMod: d [
        | q rem i part |
        q := LargePositiveInteger basicNew: self size.
        rem := 0.
        i := self size.
        [ i >= 1 ] whileTrue: [
            part := (rem * 256) + (self byteAt: i).
            q byteAt: i put: (part // d).
            rem := part \\ d.
            i := i - 1 ].
        ^Association key: q normalize value: rem
    ]
]

"I am a LargeInteger that is zero or greater: my class IS the plus
 sign. All real behavior lives in LargeInteger; only what depends on
 sign (such as printing without a leading minus) distinguishes me."

LargeInteger subclass: LargePositiveInteger [
]

"I am a LargeInteger below zero: my class IS the minus sign, and my
 bytes store the plain magnitude, not a twos-complement encoding. All
 real behavior lives in LargeInteger; only what depends on sign (such
 as printing the leading minus) distinguishes me."

LargeInteger subclass: LargeNegativeInteger [
]
